'''Guayaquil City F.C.''' (known as ''C.D. River Ecuador'' until 2017) is an [[Ecuador]]ian professional football club based in [[Guayaquil]]. They currently play in the country's first-level football league&mdash;the [[Serie A de Ecuador|Serie A]]&mdash;after gaining promotion from the segunda-level Primera Categoria.

==History==
[[File:River Plate Ecuador logo.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The badge of River Ecuador, 2010–2012]]
Formed in 2007 as ''Club Deportivo River Plate Ecuador'' (or ''River Ecuador''), the club was founded through a partnership with the dominant [[Argentina|Argentinian]] side [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].<ref name="RiverEcuador">{{cite web |url=https://deportes.elpais.com/deportes/2015/12/18/actualidad/1450478328_107679.html |title=Los cuatro River de América |trans-title=The Four River of the Americas |work=[[El País]] |date=19 December 2015 |accessdate=14 July 2017 |language=ES}}</ref> By 2010 the relationship had already ended, but the club continued to operate under its given name and with River Plate's traditional red kit colour.<ref name="RiverEcuador"/>

On 11 July 2017 it was announced that River Ecuador had renamed themselves to ''Guayaquil City Fútbol Club'', changing their strip to sky blue and white horizontal stripes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/2017/07/11/nota/6275965/river-ecuador-jugara-este-viernes-como-guayaquil-city-fc |title=River Ecuador jugará desde este viernes como Guayaquil City FC |trans-title=River Ecuador will play from this Friday as Guayaquil City FC |work=[[El Universo]] |date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=14 July 2017 }}</ref> The new name, kit colours and badge design prompted a number of claims that the change in identity was the result of a takeover by the [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]-linked [[City Football Group]], though no evidence of this was forthcoming.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://depor.com/futbol-internacional/resto-del-mundo/guayaquil-city-fc-oficializo-primera-filial-manchester-city-sudamerica-42030 |title=Guayaquil City FC es la primera filial del Manchester de Pep Guardiola en Sudamérica |trans-title=Guayaquil City FC is the first affiliate of Pep Guardiola's Manchester in South America |work=depor.com |date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=14 July 2017 }}</ref>

